## Architecture Review

### Your Goal (rephrased clearly)
1. Mobile → backs up health_connect_export.zip to Google Drive
2. That zip lands in GCS (Google Cloud Storage) automatically
3. A pipeline extracts it, migrates to DuckDB/Parquet, loads into analytics DB
4. Grafana visualizes it, BigQuery/DuckDB queries it, an LLM reads the analysis

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━


### The Core Problem with Google Drive Trigger

Google Drive does not natively push to GCS or Pub/Sub. You have two realistic options:

| Option | How | Free? | Complexity |
|---|---|---|---|
| Drive → GCS via rclone on Cloud Run Job (scheduled) | Cloud Scheduler triggers Cloud Run every X hours, rclone syncs Drive→GCS | ✅ Yes | Low |
| Drive → GCS via Google Apps Script webhook | Apps Script watches Drive file changes, calls a Cloud Run HTTP endpoint | ✅ Yes | Medium |
| Drive API push notifications | Drive API channel webhook → Pub/Sub → Cloud Run | ✅ Yes | High, but proper event-driven |

Recommendation: Option 3 (Drive API push → Pub/Sub → Cloud Run) — it's the right architecture and fits always-free tiers.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━


### Revised Architecture (Always-Free)

Mobile App (Health Connect)
        ↓  backup zip
   Google Drive
        ↓  Drive API push notification (free)
   Cloud Pub/Sub  ←──────────────────────────────┐
        ↓  trigger                                │
   Cloud Run (extractor)                          │
        ↓  download zip from Drive                │
   Cloud Storage (GCS)  ←── stores .db + parquet  │
        ↓  GCS Pub/Sub notification               │
   Cloud Run (migrator) ──── runs migrate script ─┘
        ↓  loads data into
   ┌────────────────────────────────────┐
   │  BigQuery (analytics + LLM input)  │  ← free 10GB/mo
   │  Firestore or AlloyDB Omni         │  ← Grafana source
   └────────────────────────────────────┘
        ↓
   Grafana (self-hosted on Cloud Run)
        ↓
   LLM context (periodic BigQuery export → Gemini/OpenAI)


━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━


### Always-Free Tier Breakdown

| Service | Free Allowance | Your Usage | Fits? |
|---|---|---|---|
| Cloud Run | 2M requests/mo, 360K CPU-sec | ~30 runs/month | ✅ |
| Cloud Storage | 5 GB standard storage | ~50 MB | ✅ |
| Pub/Sub | 10 GB messages/mo | negligible | ✅ |
| Cloud Scheduler | 3 jobs/mo | 1 job | ✅ |
| BigQuery | 10 GB storage, 1 TB queries/mo | ~50 MB, tiny queries | ✅ |
| Artifact Registry | 0.5 GB | small images | ✅ |
| Drive API | free | free | ✅ |

Grafana: Run on Cloud Run (free tier) using a persistent volume, or use Grafana Cloud free tier (3 users, 10K metrics).

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━


### Database Strategy (no overlap, purpose-specific)

| DB | Role | Why |
|---|---|---|
| GCS Parquet files | raw archive / source of truth | cheap, durable, replayable |
| BigQuery | analytics + LLM context queries | SQL at scale, free tier huge |
| InfluxDB OSS on Cloud Run or PostgreSQL (AlloyDB Omni) | Grafana time-series source | Grafana has native connectors |
| (skip DuckDB in cloud) | local analysis only | no managed cloud offering |

Actually the simplest Grafana path: BigQuery → Grafana directly. Grafana has a BigQuery plugin. One DB for both analytics and visualization.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━


### Recommended Build Order

Phase 1 — Data pipeline (GCS + Cloud Run)
  1. GCS bucket setup
  2. Drive API watch → Pub/Sub topic
  3. Cloud Run: download zip from Drive → extract → upload .db to GCS
  4. GCS notification → Pub/Sub → Cloud Run: run migration → upload Parquet

Phase 2 — Analytics
  5. Cloud Run: load Parquet → BigQuery tables (bq load, free)
  6. BigQuery views matching your v_steps_daily, v_heart_rate, etc.

Phase 3 — Visualization
  7. Grafana Cloud (free) connected to BigQuery

Phase 4 — LLM integration
  8. Cloud Scheduler weekly job: BigQuery → summary JSON → feed to LLM API


━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━


### One concern to flag

Drive API push notifications require a publicly reachable HTTPS endpoint (your Cloud Run URL) and need to be renewed every 7 days (a limitation of the 
Drive API). The renewal can be automated inside Cloud Run itself, so it's not a blocker — just something to build in from the start.

